title: How to let employee use a USA app in another country when VPN’s don’t work?
author: IwilldiedailyforGOD
text:
Hi everybody,

I hired a lady from Egypt to help me out with my business. I mainly use the sites OfferUp and Facebook marketplace, I haven’t checked Facebook yet but we have run into issues with her not being able to use OfferUp at all. Here are the issues:

1) OfferUp isn’t available in her country

2) we tried changing locations on her iPhone, she was able to download the app, but now the app says she is “outside the country”

3) we tried a VPN, but it appears OfferUp is blocking anything like that to prevent scammers


I’m thinking we’d have to set up a proxy from the little information I’ve gathered online, since OfferUp sends HTTPS requests to a mobile device to verify it is what it says it is, so a proxy is supposed to help do that. Problem though is, I’m not sure if there are any other solutions or how to even set up a proxy if need be. 

Could anyone help me down the right path? Thanks a lot for any tips!
